						               													<description>Capital Talouspeli (economy game) is a Finnish Monopoly-like economy game manufactured by Nelostuote Oy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;From the box (translated from Finnish):&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Make business in stock markets or gamble with savings and interests.&amp;#10;As a real estate agent you buy and build estates and make money with them. As an investor you buy stocks, gain power for general meetings, or maybe you just do some cornering.&amp;#10;To win the game you must have right profile, strategy and tactics, but luck is involved in both good and bad. There are limitless number of player roles. You can thrive in many ways, as in real life.&amp;#10;When necessary, you have to change your chosen tactics and strategy. Inherited assets and lottery prizes can make surprising changes in the game. Wealthy players may buy their very own jet plane and fly around the world from business to business. Illegal businesses may sound nice, but risks are great.&amp;#10;Your game doesn't end in bankruptcy! After the debt restructuring it's still possible for you to win the game. The game may even be used to educate company management.&amp;#10;Have fun while developing your strategical, tactical and psychological skills.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
